Series III
Write a program to generate the first 'n' terms of the following series 6, 11, 21, 36, 56,...
Input Format:

The input is an integer 'n' which denotes the number of terms to be printed in the series.

Output Format:

Print the series and refer the sample output for formatting.

Sample Input:

6

Sample Output:

6 11 21 36 56 81

Case 1
Case 2
Case 3
Input (stdin)
3

Output (stdout)
6 11 21

Input (stdin)
10

Output (stdout)
6 11 21 36 56 81 111 146 186 231

Input (stdin)
2

Output (stdout)
6 11

PROGRAM IN CPP

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() 
{
  int n,x=6;
  cin>>n;
  for(int i=1;i<=n;i++)
  {
    cout<<x<<" ";
    x = x + 5*i;
  }
  return 0;
}
